devdoc.details: Demonstrates how to add pausing to the Bonding contract.

bond(uint256).details: Marked `whenNotPaused`. If the contract is paused, this function      will revert. The owner can call `pause()`/`unpause()` as needed.

params.tokenAmount: The amount of `paymentToken` the user is depositing.

params._paymentToken: Address of the ERC20 token used for bonding (DAI, USDC, etc.).
params._roboMoney: Address of the RoboMoney token (replaces mlAMPL).
params._targetPrice: Base price ratio for RoboMoney vs. payment token.

pause().details: Owner can pause contract functions protected by `whenNotPaused`.

withdraw(address,uint256,address).details: Owner can withdraw any ERC20 tokens (e.g. leftover paymentToken or minted RoboMoney).Not protected by `whenNotPaused`, since an owner might need       to withdraw tokens even if contract is paused for bonding.

params.recipient: Recipient address to receive the tokens.
params.token: Address of the ERC20 token to withdraw.
